column1: 4849684 - failed XML load from TAF to 42Q
column37:
Hi Team,

This was a nokia custom api developed in 2017 and the plant used 42qprtl1 host to access custom api under nokia-custom-api. Since we shutdown 42qprtl1 in august 2021 plant have reported the issue. While analysing we found that this was moved to mes-api in [production.42-q.com/production-api2|http://production.42-q.com/production-api2] long back but plant was still using 42qprtl1 host.

Plant have tested the 2 mes-apis and taf/submitTestResults  is not working.

[https://production.42-q.com/mes-api/index.html#/taf/submitTestResults|https://production.42-q.com/mes-api/index.html#/taf/submitTestResults] -------> THis is not sending the files to the parser. (*The server encountered an unexpected condition that prevented it from fulfilling the request.)*
[https://production.42-q.com/mes-api/index.html#/taf/getRackGenealogy|https://production.42-q.com/mes-api/index.html#/taf/getRackGenealogy]  -------------> This works fine as per the user.

Please create a JIRA for Welinton team to check why the below API is not working. Test details attached for the reference. Please let us know in case of any information needed from us.

column37:
Hi Team,

The plant E81 reported an issue with the customized parser: HATTERAS which does not work properly.

Details:
Measurement:  [https://production-meas.42-q.com/Instance/Parser/Default.aspx|https://production-meas.42-q.com/Instance/Parser/Default.aspx]
Parser:             MES42Q.Measurement.Parser.Hatteras.Processor_3_0_0_0.dll
Conduit:           corpconduit3.sanmina.com
Serial:              LBADVA71213400004

Description:
We found that the Hatteras parser can not process the log file properly through the Conduit server if the serial number already exists other component ID. We always get the error "Expected:
AddNontrackedAssemblyComponent with answers to the following prompt(s):Software? \[component_id]", see images below.


!image-20210914-093358.png|width=1331,height=798!

!image-20210914-093418.png|width=1322,height=858!

Checked the conduit log, see below for details.

2021-09-13 09:57:51,290 info \{asio - [10.180.11.227:57448|http://10.180.11.227:57448/]} Response: Id: <90b19efd-2bbf-40e7-a19e-f7dd738dd420> Client Id <p5523dc1> Employee <999999> Device <938> Transaction Status: <OK> Transaction Unit: Unit Id <LBADVA71213400004> Part Number <LFGUSF101206-200> Quantity <1> Revision <2.02> 2021-09-13 09:57:51,297 info \{asio - [10.180.11.227:57450|http://10.180.11.227:57450/]} Request: Id: <f56d9508-4537-40dc-b7fe-406d475d57af> Client Id <p5523dc1> Employee <999999> Device <938> linger: 0 single transaction: 0 Unit Id <LBADVA71213400004> Part Number <> Quantity <0> Revision <>> Client Command(s): ReplaceComponent <component_id: R11.6.1> <old_component_id: 84C80744FC00> -- Here is wrong, The component_id: 84C80744FC00 is added for process:Function Test not the process: Add Software Revision. END 2021-09-13 09:57:51,466 info \{asio - [10.180.11.227:57450|http://10.180.11.227:57450/]} Response: Id: <f56d9508-4537-40dc-b7fe-406d475d57af> Client Id <p5523dc1> Employee <999999> Device <938> Transaction Status: <ERROR> --> Expected: AddNontrackedAssemblyComponent with answers to the following prompt(s): Software? <component_id> Transaction Unit: Unit Id <LBADVA71213400004> Part Number <LFGUSF101206-200> Quantity <1> Revision <2.02> <OK> --> Removed Component Id <84C80744FC00> at Reference Designator <MAC_Address> from unit <LBADVA71213400004> <ERROR> --> Unable to find serial record for Component Id <R11.6.1> <OK> --> PASS to SFQC - <Passed> unit <LBADVA71213400004> from <S638 SCSW Software> to <SFQC Final QC>

03/Aug/21 6:32 PM;557058:53d818a9-472e-4e81-bf75-003946f0d68d;[~accountid:5d2e2d07f3471e0c800c6279] 

As we talked, API Gateway should be updated with the same swagger used to configure AWS Gateway.

This endpoint [+https://apigateway-prod.42-q.com/mes-api/sfdc_beus_sv/shop-orders/R-AE01403-2131-R08/release-non-serialized?employeeNumber=test&shopOrderQuantity=300+|https://apigateway-prod.42-q.com/mes-api/sfdc_beus_sv/shop-orders/R-AE01403-2131-R08/release-non-serialized?employeeNumber=test&shopOrderQuantity=300]   was removed from the api and was replaced by:

POST /\{target}/shop-orders/release/\{type}

!image-20210803-223019.png|width=83.33333333333333%!

This endpoint has all the validations and releases the Shop Order in a asynchronous way, using Tinmon.



FYI

[https://sdk.42-q.com/docs/42q-mes-api/1/routes/\{target}/shop-orders/release/\{type}/post|https://sdk.42-q.com/docs/42q-mes-api/1/routes/%7Btarget%7D/shop-orders/release/%7Btype%7D/post]

column1: UAT: Exception when wip move for when done/leaving a mapped op seq is enabled and no map
column37: When ERP wip move configuration to do a wip move when leaving a mapped location is enabled and the shop order's ERP route is not mapped, a postgres null exception occurs when a serial on the shop order has  it’s location changed. The gen attribute for the configuration is table "wip_movement" and attribute name "do_leave_move" with value of true to have it enabled.

20/May/21 3:06 AM;557058:72276612-3fc8-4106-b100-91843865da74;[~accountid:5ab5521333719f2a50171fb1] [~accountid:5a5d4ef71b40574bc477c625] 

Version 15.69 don’t  change any low layer logic. Just switch tomcat/JDK version.

So I suggest to change tomcat start  environment

vi /usr/local/tomcat/bin/setenv.sh  and replace GC_OPTS and MEMORY_OPTS

GC_OPTS="-Dsun.rmi.dgc.server.gcInterval=2147483646 -XX:+DisableExplicitGC -XX:+ExplicitGCInvokesConcurrent -XX:+UseCompressedOops -XX:+UseCompressedClassPointers -XX:+UseG1GC -XX:MaxGCPauseMillis=1000 -XX:+UseStringDeduplication -XX:+ScavengeBeforeFullGC -XX:+CMSClassUnloadingEnabled -XX:+ExplicitGCInvokesConcurrentAndUnloadsClasses -verbose:gc -Xloggc:$\{CATALINA_BASE}/logs/gc.log -XX:+PrintGCDetails -XX:+PrintGCDateStamps -XX:+PrintTenuringDistribution -XX:+PrintStringDeduplicationStatistics -XX:+UseGCLogFileRotation -XX:NumberOfGCLogFiles=10 -XX:GCLogFileSize=10m"

MEMORY_OPTS="-server -Xshare:auto -Xms4096m -Xmx4096m -XX:MaxMetaspaceSize=512m -XX:LargePageSizeInBytes=128m -XX:+UseFastAccessorMethods"

Reference  from 

[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1VuNy2V7Jge3PnMD3hcS5ubNXwB60w0Kfio1peY5eiMU/edit#|https://docs.google.com/document/d/1VuNy2V7Jge3PnMD3hcS5ubNXwB60w0Kfio1peY5eiMU/edit#|smart-link]

column277:
01/Jun/21 3:31 PM;5ab5521333719f2a50171fb1;Ticket ID: 8064 Note Added by Elena Romero  in Freshdesk: Merged from ticket 8224  
      Subject: Fwd: About corpmesspc3 issue  
      Description:  
 Team,  
   
 Please raise a Jira to Monica Sheik, so we can get UAT non medical for Sanmina patched with the below info shared by  Jack Mo. 
   
 It is related to the high CPU utilization issue that SPC is causing after upgrade Open JDK from 1.7 to 1.8 during 42Q upgrade to 15.69. 
   
 This is related to Jira MPDI-3209 assigned to Eng. 
   
 Thanks 
         
   
 ____________________________________ 
 Carlos E. Romero | 42Q | +52 3310 140970 
         
   
 ---------- Forwarded message --------- From: mo jack <jack.mo@42-q.com> Date: Mon, May 31, 2021 at 10:22 PM Subject: Re: About corpmesspc3 issue To: Carlos Romero [42-Q] <carlos.romero@42-q.com> Cc: Gary Li <gary.li@42-q.com>, Fabio Pelissoni <fabio.pelissoni@42-q.com>, Nanting Sun <nanting.sun@42-q.com>, DL-DevOps <dl-devops@42-q.com> 
 
   
 Team 
     I think I  found the cause of the CPU high loading. 
     By analyze file   threaddump-20210525-0159    I am sure jfree chart call  layer code to draw line will consume more CPU.　And this don't trigger problem in Oracle JDK 1.7 
    corpmesspc3,corpmesspc4,corpmesspc5 have been updated to open-jdk 1.8.  For fixed this problem need to to below step 
   
          1. Download  marlin-0.9.4.3-Unsafe.jar    and upload to  coprmesspc3/4/5 /usr/local/tomcat/lib          2. Change setenv.sh  append              JAVA2D_RENDERER="-Dsun.java2d.renderer=org.marlin.pisces.DMarlinRenderingEngine"            BOOT_CLASSPATH="-Xbootclasspath/a:/usr/local/tomcat/lib/marlin-0.9.4.3-Unsafe.jar" 
 
 JAVA_OPTS="$JAVA2D_RENDERER  $BOOT_CLASSPATH  $SPC_SERVER_ENVIRONMENT $PORTAL_URL $RDS_URL $RDS_USERNAME $RDS_PASSWORD $RDS_INITIALSIZE $RDS_MAXACTIVE $RDS_MINACTIVE" 
         3. Restart tomcat service  
 
   
     
 
  
  
   
   
   
   
   
 Reference  https://github.com/adoptium/temurin-build/issues/716
 
 Local testing  screen shot 
   
 High consume CPU 

 
 
    
 Normal working 
     Best Regards Jack Mo CDC (Shenzhen, China)    
    
   
 Carlos Romero [42-Q] <carlos.romero@42-q.com> 于2021年5月28日周五 上午7:05写道： 
 
 
 
 Team 
   
 Yesterday it was deployed a tomcat monitor script in SPC servers. So far we have received 10 notifications about tomcat was using a lot of CPU for 10 minutes, hence it was restarted. also we have not received notifications about issues in SPC3 server. 
   
 One of the E38 sites was pointed to use SPC4 instead of SPC3 and since then, the performance issues are also appearing in SPC4. 
   
 I hope this additional info helps 
         
   
 ____________________________________ 
 Carlos E. Romero | 42Q | +52 3310 140970 
         
 
 
  
 On Wed, May 26, 2021 at 8:04 PM Gary Li <gary.li@42-q.com> wrote: 
 
 
 Hi Fabio,    
 If we can add more CPU and memory to corpmesspc3 that should be the better solution for the current issue because the old hardware and tomcat will bring back some vulnerabilities issues.  
 
   
 Thanks. 
   
   
 
  
 On Wed, May 26, 2021 at 11:29 PM Fabio Pelissoni <fabio.pelissoni@42-q.com> wrote: 
 
 
 Jack,   
 Still not sure why an old server and an old tomcat will be better with the 15.69 version.  
 You mentioned that the issue is when export PNG images. Is this an application functionality or Tomcat your application calls?  As I know, no other plants are complaining, and looks this issue is happening with one scenario that E38 is trying to do. If we do the same scenario in the old server (hardware) and old tomcat. are we not going to have the same problem? 
   
 Just trying to understand the issue here. We may try to add more memory or CPU to corpmesspc3 if necessary but back to the old hardware and tomcat will bring back some vulnerabilities issues we had. 
   
 Regards,    
 
________________________________________________________ 
 
   
 Fabio Pelissoni Sr Application Development/DevOps Manager | 42Q | Huntsville, AL  
 (O): +1 256 882-4731 | (M): +1 256 513-1385  
   
 
 
 
  
 On Wed, May 26, 2021 at 4:01 AM mo jack <jack.mo@42-q.com> wrote: 
 
 
 
 Hi Fabio 
      Recently we continuous watching  corpmesspc3,corpmesspc4,corpmesspc5. 
      The corpmesspc3 often raise up hight CPU consume. These have relation with sites  mes_e38_01, mes_e38_02. 
      With the help from support team,  mes_e38_01, mes_e38_02 will migrate to corpmespc4, corpmesspc5. And this action is short time solution. 
      From the program side version 15.69 SPC server  only changes the  send hold method. But we locate  CPU high consume threads  is all about export PNG(image). So version 15.69 version should not lead to CPU high loading. 
      For avoid site mes_e38_01,mes_e38_02 create fatal problem I suggest   restart old machine (10.180.11.204 old  corpmesspc3)   and upgrade to version 15.69. Migrate mes_e38_01 mes_e38_02 to  10.180.11.204. 
 　Of course  this is a short solution  and we will continue to spend time resolving this issue. 
   
      JIRA# https://sanmina.atlassian.net/browse/MPDI-3209
 
   
   
    Best Regards Jack Mo CDC (Shenzhen, China)      
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

 

--

30/Mar/21 9:34 AM;557058:e985e556-7ff0-4bf4-a720-6e6d22712971;[~accountid:5aa271ef460f54375e34da4e] [~accountid:557058:4584bc53-9882-4708-a327-8299d61f108e]    I did some research on this today.  -Seems that they are talking about a Sample by Attribute plan,  and it does look like it does not auto_populate (which I think is what the AutoCreate on the portlet refers to).   Based on a simple grep of the code, the sample types that support auto_populate in conduit appear to be:-

-sample_part_number.sql-
-sample_procedure.sql-
-sample_shop_order.sql-
-sample_workstation.sql-

Have researched more,  working with Edgar Gonzalez to test.  I was wrong about initial assessment.  Sample types that do not auto populate new plans directly do support it by calling sample_part_number.

[~accountid:557058:0794a087-3aea-4fdf-8299-388e6e778dd0] is working to not have this parameter required in be-custom-api. This will be included on the PROD upgrade.

The reason why this is not happening in PROD:
This new parameter was added on the changes done in the IC/Seal Print forms on 2019. The be-custom-api uses the same dependency, this way we can make sure that the api and form have the same behavior. What happen was that the cell-manufacturing form was update, but the dependency that be-custom-api uses was not updated back then.

And it is happening in UAT:
Last year we fixed a lot of open issues for cell-manufacturing and be-custom-api and we put the latest dependency. That's why this is only happening in the UAT.

Issue:
We have problems applying some types of samples with PWB:
AT (Attribute)
CP (Component)
DEF (Defect Code)
PFM (Part Family Master)
PM (Part Mask)
SM (Serial Mask)
DEF (Defect Code), WS (Workstation) only in data collector

[https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/11Xf-I5Irt3lB-5-qq1pSZ75ps6gGFzytB6WE5TeM8-4/edit?usp=sharing|https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/11Xf-I5Irt3lB-5-qq1pSZ75ps6gGFzytB6WE5TeM8-4/edit?usp=sharing]

column267:
16/Dec/20 6:32 PM;557058:e985e556-7ff0-4bf4-a720-6e6d22712971;This issue is caused by the mes_gbs_test database having a sample_plan record for an attribute sample that has a tag containing ****.     The asterisks caused a problem in the regexp operation in the query, which resulted in the wrong index being used.  A like_str around the tag value seemed to resolve this.

But  I have also seen cases where the regexp would return  an error, like below:

mes_gbs_test=> select sp.*from sample_plan sp
where sp.sample_master_key = 119 and
'ENGTESTPART2' ~ like_str(sp.tag)    *--- tag has “FSC.*****”*
order by sp.sequence limit 1;
*ERROR:  invalid regular expression: quantifier operand invalid*

I am not sure that the ~ operation works exactly like grep that is used in the SFDC sampling,   We may need to handle these errors in a more friendly manner, or test when the tags and masks are added in the portlet.

column281:
23/Feb/22 10:06 AM;557058:e985e556-7ff0-4bf4-a720-6e6d22712971;[~accountid:5ab5521333719f2a50171fb1] [~accountid:557058:4584bc53-9882-4708-a327-8299d61f108e] 

We have found an issue with the Part-Family Master and it will be corrected in 15.73

The part mask and serial mask both use a Regex mask,  just as the legacy version does.  Not an sfdc style of mask.    

So for the Serial Mask test they ran,  the mask should be “ITTEST\[0-9]\{7}”    

For the Part Mask test, they should test with “QCPPART\\w\{6}”

column1: 4562506 - Shipment Report for Mentor not found any data from PTSR
column37:
Hi Support team,

E91 reported they couldn't get any PTSR data in the mentor report created
by below crontab job on *Oct 2nd*.
*/15 * * * * /mes/mds/bin/mentor_e92_01_rpt.ksh mes_e91_01
>/mes/mds/reports/mentor/mentor_report_err.log 2>&1
MDS: corpmes6/mes_e91_01
MESR: corpmesr11as/mesr_91
PTSR: corpmesr5/PTSR_E91

The crontab job calls the function df_mentor_shiprpt_e92 to get the report,
if we check the function we can see it uses below query, it couldn't get
any data from PTSR

*with delivery as
(
select distinct sn.delivery_number "Delivery
Note",sn.customer_po_number "PO Number",sn.so_line "PO Line",
p.part_number "Material Number",p.description
"Description",count(ser.serial_number) "Qty",'EA' "UoM",
ser.serial_number as serial_number_top,ser.serial_key,
DENSE_RANK() OVER(partition by sn.delivery_number
order by sn.so_line) "Line ID",
0 "Level",sn.source_key
from serial ser
inner join part p on ser.part_key=p.part_key and ser.source_key=p.source_key
inner join ship_notify sn on ser.ship_notify_key=sn.ship_notify_key
and ser.source_key=sn.source_key
where p.part_number like 'LFMT%'
and sn.ship_ts > '2020-10-02 00:00:00'  and sn.ship_ts < '2020-10-03 00:00:00'	
and ser.unit_status_key =40
and  ser.container_serial_key is not null
group by sn.delivery_number,sn.customer_po_number,sn.so_line,p.part_number,p.description,ser.serial_number,
ser.serial_key,sn.source_key	

),
deliveryChild as
(
select "Delivery Note","PO Number","PO Line", "Material Number",
"Description", "Qty", "UoM"::text,serial_number_top "Serial
Number","Line ID", "Level" from delivery
union
select d."Delivery Note",d."PO Number",d."PO Line", d."Material
Number", d."Description", d."Qty", d."UoM"::text,s.serial_number
"Serial Number",d."Line ID", d."Level"
from delivery d
inner join component c on d.serial_key=c.serial_key and
d.source_key=c.source_key
inner join serial s on c.component_id=s.serial_number and
c.source_key=s.source_key
inner join part p on p.part_key=s.part_key
where p.part_number like 'LFMT%'
and s.unit_status_key=60
and c.removed=0
),
PTSR as
(
select * from
dblink('host=' || (select value from appsettings where key='ptsr_server') ||
' dbname=' || (select value from appsettings where
key='ptsr_dbname') ||
' port=' || (select value from appsettings where key='ptsr_port') ||
' user=' || (select value from appsettings where key='ptsr_user') ||
' password=' || (select value from appsettings where
key='ptsr_password'),'select distinct pn.part_number, pn.description,
comp.lot_code,
ISNULL(NULLIF(comp.lot_code,''UNDEFINED''),ISNULL(comp.date_code_str,''
'') ) as "Lot_Code2", scan.barcode as "barcode",1 "Level",
pl.designator
from scanning_1 scan
inner join load_component_1 lc on (abs(scan.ws_id)=lc.ws_id or
scan.ws_id=-lc.ws_id) and scan.scan_time > lc.up_time AND
(lc.down_time > scan.scan_time or lc.down_time=0)
inner join component_1 comp on comp.component_id = lc.component_id
inner join incoming i on i.incoming_id= comp.incoming_id
inner join part_number pn on pn.pn_id = i.pn_id
inner join pick_list_item pl on pl.pick_list_id=scan.pick_list_id
and lc.station_id = pl.station_id
where pn.part_number like ''LFMT-%'' and upper(pn.description) like
''%CRYSTAL CHIP 3%''
and pl.designator in
(''CRY3_00'',''CRY3_01'',''CRY3_02'',''CRY3_03'',''CRY3_04'',''CRY3_05'',''CRY3_06'',''CRY3_07'')
and ' ||
(
select  'pn.part_number like ''LFMT-%'' and
upper(pn.description) like ''%CRYSTAL CHIP 3%'' and scan.barcode in ('

||array_to_string(array_agg ( ''''||substring("Serial Number" from
position(' ' in "Serial Number")+1 for length("Serial Number"))||

'''' ),',') || ')' from deliveryChild
) || ' group by
pn.part_number,pn.description,comp.lot_code,"Lot_Code2",scan.barcode,
pl.designator'

) as ptsr (part_number text, description text, lot_code text,
"Lot_Code2" text,"barcode" text, "Level" int, designator text)
)

select * from PTSR*

----------------------------------There is no record

However the data exists
Example SN: 1.3/1.3 261630 SDIP-610607
\[image: image.png]

dblink('host=' || (select value from appsettings where key='ptsr_server')

||' dbname='||(select value from appsettings where

) as "Lot_Code2", scan.barcode as "barcode",1 "Level", pl.designator from

*_) || ' group by pn.part_number,pn.description,comp.lot_code,"Lot_Code2",scan.barcode, pl.designator'_*

) as ptsr (part_number text, description text, lot_code text, "Lot_Code2" text,"barcode" text, "Level" int, designator text)



h2. *Query fixed:* 



select * from
dblink('host=' || (select value from appsettings where key='ptsr_server') ||
' dbname=' || (select value from appsettings where key='ptsr_dbname') ||
' port=' || (select value from appsettings where key='ptsr_port') ||
' user=' || (select value from appsettings where key='ptsr_user') ||
' password=' || (select value from appsettings where key='ptsr_password'),'select distinct pn.part_number, pn.description, comp.lot_code,
ISNULL(NULLIF(comp.lot_code,''UNDEFINED''),ISNULL(comp.date_code_str,'' '') ) as "Lot_Code2", scan.barcode as "barcode",1 "Level", pl.designator
from scanning_1 scan
inner join load_component_1 lc on (abs(scan.ws_id)=lc.ws_id or scan.ws_id=-lc.ws_id) and scan.scan_time > lc.up_time AND (lc.down_time > scan.scan_time or lc.down_time=0)
inner join component_1 comp on comp.component_id = lc.component_id
inner join incoming i on i.incoming_id= comp.incoming_id
inner join part_number pn on pn.pn_id = i.pn_id
inner join pick_list_item pl on pl.pick_list_id=scan.pick_list_id and lc.station_id = pl.station_id
where pn.part_number like ''LFMT-%'' and upper(pn.description) like ''%CRYSTAL CHIP 3%''
and pl.designator in (''CRY3_00'',''CRY3_01'',''CRY3_02'',''CRY3_03'',''CRY3_04'',''CRY3_05'',''CRY3_06'',''CRY3_07'')
*_and scan.barcode in (' || (select  array_to_string(array_agg ( '''' || serial_numberd || '''' ),',') from deliveryChild)  || '_*)'
) as ptsr (part_number text, description text, lot_code text, "Lot_Code2" text,"barcode" text, "Level" int, designator text)
)

The options that I see now are: 

* Wait for Casey to ask her about that logic, probably the units processed on Oct 2 have something missing or confirm if is a bug. 
* If is urgent for the plant the fix then will be necessary setup the new function and the environment in UAT and the plant need to validate all the scenarios to see this change is not breaking any scenario that already works in their side. 

If you have any other suggestion guys, please let me know. 

Thanks,

Felipe.

Yet it started working immediately after the plant changed those to Released.      Side note,  I dont see p1405dc1 log on corpconduit3.  I wanted to see if a Hold would have been logged. column1: Target HPU vs SOMs Target Discrepancies
column37:
Hello,

Customer noticed some issues with the target HPUs set for some part numbers.

 There are variations between what was entered in the SOMs target and what appears in the OEE WB target.

It seems like the Target HPU set for the C-location (3rd OP) is showing up at the B-location (2nd OP)

Here's an example:

SOMs target for DV065661 at B256

!image-20200813-223849.png|width=1024,height=163!

Target HPU at OEE WB for the same part at the same location

!image-20200813-223859.png|width=1255,height=942!

B-location target is 25200 (7 hours) but it's taking the target of the C-location 16200 (4.5 hours).

Regards,
column266:
13/Aug/20 6:42 PM;5d2e2d07f3471e0c800c6279;[~accountid:5e4ea968a17f930c9b952794]  help us to do some test on UAT env.

Did additional testing in UAT. When updating existing lines, it adds a new line instead of overwriting and updating the existing line.

* In some cases, no changes were made. The current table was downloaded and new lines added.
** The issue- This has caused thousands of duplicates.
* When changes were made to the target, it added a new line with the same mfg line, PN, process & location but an updated target.
** The issue- On OEE WB, it shows the original target instead of the updated one.

Here's a screenshot from UAT

!image-20200813-224119.png|width=1384,height=580!

In production, there are 7 duplicate lines of DV065661 at B256

!image-20200813-224150.png|width=1344,height=260!

Regards.

column270:
25/Aug/20 2:03 PM;5e4ea968a17f930c9b952794;[~accountid:557058:53d818a9-472e-4e81-bf75-003946f0d68d] Initially, the customer was exporting the entire table, adding new lines and uploading daily. This caused the duplicate lines so I exported the entire table and removed all the duplicates. I then deleted the existing table & re-uploaded the clean version. I instructed the user to only add new lines so there should be no more duplicates. I also told them if an update to an existing target is required, to edit in the table instead of uploading another line.

The soms_target table matched the file I uploaded.  However the customer continues to see the machine target times instead of setup in the setup locations on the OEE workbench.
column271:

column272:

[~accountid:5e4ea968a17f930c9b952794] 

If there are duplicate lines, OEE Workbench will consider the first line added, never the last one. [~accountid:557058:bfa3b126-fb54-4e0f-bdcd-6175679f8ac3]  Can you please confirm that?

FYI

[~accountid:557058:bc8b9612-3abe-41a0-bfa7-f89f184be2bf]
column273:
25/Aug/20 2:56 PM;5e4ea968a17f930c9b952794;This is on STL Production. I removed almost 12K duplicate lines on Aug 13 when I created a new upload. But there needs to be a way to upload updates without duplicates or skip duplicates. They add several new routes everyday so it’s challenging for them to confirm that a line s not already been created.  I’ve just checked and there are now 300 duplicates after I removed them all 2 weeks ago. 

[~accountid:557058:bc8b9612-3abe-41a0-bfa7-f89f184be2bf] HPU targets on SQC have been configured. My understanding is that is required for OEE reports to work.
column274: 25/Aug/20 3:58 PM;557058:bc8b9612-3abe-41a0-bfa7-f89f184be2bf;[~accountid:5e4ea968a17f930c9b952794] we are working with CSE on a temporary solution to remove duplicate entries.
column275:
25/Aug/20 6:35 PM;557058:bfa3b126-fb54-4e0f-bdcd-6175679f8ac3;[~accountid:5e4ea968a17f930c9b952794] [~accountid:557058:53d818a9-472e-4e81-bf75-003946f0d68d] [~accountid:557058:8e968b5a-0955-4f2d-b214-3a3e903c02cd] That’s a correct assumption. OEE Workbench will get the first occurrence it finds on soms_target table.

We’re also implementing a temp solution as Welinton mentioned that will remove in background duplicated entries on soms_target table keeping the newest ones. This will come earlier next week on UAT.

column1: F&C lower case issue (BE)
column37:
Hello Team, 
Could you help us to take a look at this case with Bloom?

The user reported below message error:

!image-20200728-205948.png|width=3072,height=1022!



The issues the case of the lots could be in the  “SK_PART-0012258” 2nd kanban serial we guess.

2 Stacks due to IC Subkit

# CM66Z09-2031-016.A.1     -   CM66Z09-000873-11              
# CM66Z09-2031-011.A.1     -   CM66Z09-000868-08

Please let us know if further info is needed.
Regards.

column1: MES API - Query Materials with "/" in name
column37:
Hi [~accountid:557058:53d818a9-472e-4e81-bf75-003946f0d68d] ,

Customer Weir TOD just raised us a case.

They want to know how to handle this scenario.

Can you please advise how to query material with / in the name entry?

E.g.
AH6/4RC00000000045

Normal entry - Failed (Obviously)
"/mes-api/weir_tod/parts/AH6/4RC00000000045"

Escape Characters - Failed also
"/mes-api/weir_tod/parts/AH6%2F4RC00000000045"

Could you help us to take a look into this ?

Regards,

Today there’s no way to handle this if the parameter is sent in the url.

column268:
22/Jun/20 11:01 AM;5a8ffcf35c7a2233512b2393;[~accountid:557058:53d818a9-472e-4e81-bf75-003946f0d68d] Amiga, can you please help with an example on how to call this API for the external, so that it will be helpful for us in future?

[~accountid:5d2e2d07f3471e0c800c6279]
column269:
22/Jun/20 1:31 PM;557058:53d818a9-472e-4e81-bf75-003946f0d68d;[~accountid:5a8ffcf35c7a2233512b2393] [~accountid:5ab5521333719f2a50171fb1] 

To be able to call mes-api in customer environments, you will need to:

* Create/Get the Palindrome Credentials for that Site
* Generate the Authorization header, [https://www.blitter.se/utils/basic-authentication-header-generator/|https://www.blitter.se/utils/basic-authentication-header-generator/]
* Using a Rest client, add the Authorization header, using the value generated in the previous step

!image-20200622-173046.png|width=1421,height=1052!



Please, let me know if you have any questions.

Thanks

column1: Cycle time reports not working (Externals, WEIR TOD)
column37:
Hi Team
Weir customer informed that Cycle time report is nor retrieving any data instead is getting an error message, Can you please see the error attached in the below image. Neither of the TOD cycletime reports are currently working. Same error for both:

!image-20200602-022819.png|width=1409,height=807!



I have taken a look on the postgres logs in the MESR server   but I could not catch any error:

No errors found from the logs in the Production environment




 From the Postgres log: (42qrpt1 :/Bkup/postgresql-logs/postgresql-01.log)

===================================

2020-06-01 18:56:32 EDT \[14369]: \[2-1] db=mesr_weir_tod,user=mesr,app=MESWeb-Execution,client=10.180.25.152 STATEMENT: -- -- MESWeb Report

* - Username: mesweb_admin
* - Report ID: 2361
* - Report Name: Cycle Time by Serial
* - Report Type: class com.sanmina.mesweb.core.models.reports.CustomReport
* - Command Name: Results

with cycle_table as (
select a.*,
((DATE_PART('day', end_ts::timestamp - start_ts::timestamp) * 24 + DATE_PART('hour', end_ts::timestamp - start_ts::timestamp)) * 60
+ DATE_PART('minute',
end_ts::timestamp - start_ts::timestamp)) * 60 + DATE_PART('second', end_ts::timestamp - start_ts::timestamp) cycle_time
from (
select hp.serial_key,s.serial_number,
hp.part_key,
s.quantity,
ha.location_key, s.source_key,
min(hp.hands_on_time) ht,
min(hp.unattended_time) ut,
min(ha.start_ts) as start_ts,
max(ha.end_ts) as end_ts
from serial s inner join hpu_process hp on s.serial_key=hp.serial_key and s.source_key=hp.source_key
inner join hpu_activity ha on hp.hpu_process_key=ha.hpu_process_key and
hp.source_key=ha.source_key where hp.part_key in (select part_key from part

* -where part_number in ('','000000000000003122','000000000000004323','000000000000004497','000000000000004686','00

0000000000004845','000000000000005105','000000000000005436','000000000000005839','000000000000006288','000000000000006290','000000000000006355','00000
0000000006718','000000000000006724','000000000000006784','000000000000006893','000000000000007978','000000000000008407','000000000000009024','00000000
0000009026','000000000000009087','000000000000009123','000000000000010178','000000000000010179','000000000000010180','000000000000010191','00000000000
0010192','000000000000010194','000000000000010195','000000000000010196','000000000000010197','000000000000010198','000000000000010199','00000000000001
0449','000000000000010450','000000000000010451','000000000000010452','000000000000010463','000000000000010464','000000000000010492','000000000000010521','000000000000010560','000000000000010583','000000000000010584','000000000000010585','000000000000010646','000000000000010838','000000000000010839','000000000000010840','000000000000010841')
)

* - and s.loc_ts between '2020-05-01 00:00:00' and '2020-05-31 23:59:59'

 group by hp.serial_key,s.serial_number,hp.part_key,ha.location_key,s.quantity,s.source_key
) a order by a.start_ts
), cycle_table2 as (
select c1.*,
( select c2.end_ts from cycle_table c2 where c2.end_ts<c1.start_ts order by c2.end_ts desc limit 1) as end_ts2
from cycle_table c1
)

select cu.customer_name as "Customer Name",
c.serial_number as "Serial Number",
c.quantity as "Serial Quantity",
p.part_number as "Part Number",
pr.process_name as "Process Name",
round(avg(c.cycle_time)) as "Cycle Time",
round(avg([c.ht|http://c.ht])) as "Hands on Time",
round(avg(c.ut)) as "Unattended Time",
round(avg(coalesce(((DATE_PART('day', start_ts::timestamp - end_ts2::timestamp) * 24 + DATE_PART('hour', start_ts::timestamp - end_ts2::timestamp)) * 60 + DATE_PART('minute', start_ts::timestamp - end_ts2::timestamp)) * 60 + DATE_PART('second', start_ts::timestamp - end_ts2::timestamp),0)) )as "Wait Time" from cycle_table2 c
inner join part p on c.part_key=p.part_key and c.source_key=p.source_key
inner join location l on c.location_key=l.location_key and c.source_key=l.source_key
inner join process pr on l.process_key=pr.process_key and l.source_key=pr.source_key
inner join customer_part cp on p.part_key=cp.part_key and p.source_key=cp.source_key
inner join customer cu on cp.customer_key=cu.customer_key group by cu.customer_name,c.serial_number,p.part_number,pr.process_name, c.quantity order by cu.customer_name,p.part_number,pr.process_name,c.serial_number



Regards.

column266: 13/Feb/20 2:26 PM;5ab5521333719f2a50171fb1;Ticket ID: 3217 Note Added by Jose Eduardo Carvajal [42-Q]  in Freshdesk: Run next function to remove all empty gen_attr  select removeGenericAttribute('location', unnest(attr_names), parent_key) from (select array_agg(attr_name) as attr_names, parent_key  from (select (getgenericattributes('location', ga.parent_key)).*  from gen_attr ga  inner join gen_attr_def gad ON ga.gen_attr_def_key = gad.gen_attr_def_key and gad.attr_name = 'shelf'  inner join mds_option mo on gad.attr_name = mo.option_value  inner join mds_option_type mot on mot.option_type = mo.option_type and gad.table_name = mot.table_name  where mot.option_type = 'flex_field_location' and mot.table_name = 'location'  and gad.attr_name in ('shelf', 'enabled', 'capacity', 'stack_type', 'part_number')  ) as shelves  where attr_data = ''  group by parent_key ) as empty_values where attr_names @> (ARRAY['shelf', 'enabled', 'capacity', 'stack_type', 'part_number']::TEXT[]);  .  .  .  (78 rows) removed.
column267:
13/Feb/20 2:27 PM;557058:53d818a9-472e-4e81-bf75-003946f0d68d;This was actually a bug, but in SFDC Configuration → Location → Copy

When the user copy a location, it is creating Flex Fields with empty values.

In order to solve this to not impact the customer uat, the following query was executed by [~accountid:5d2e2d07f3471e0c800c6279] 



select removeGenericAttribute('location', unnest(attr_names), parent_key)
from (select array_agg(attr_name) as attr_names, parent_key
 from (select (getgenericattributes('location', ga.parent_key)).*
 from gen_attr ga
 inner join gen_attr_def gad ON ga.gen_attr_def_key = gad.gen_attr_def_key and gad.attr_name = 'shelf'
 inner join mds_option mo on gad.attr_name = mo.option_value
 inner join mds_option_type mot on mot.option_type = mo.option_type and gad.table_name = mot.table_name
 where mot.option_type = 'flex_field_location' and mot.table_name = 'location'
 and gad.attr_name in ('shelf', 'enabled', 'capacity', 'stack_type', 'part_number')
 ) as shelves
 where attr_data = ''
 group by parent_key
) as empty_values
where attr_names @> (ARRAY\['shelf', 'enabled', 'capacity', 'stack_type', 'part_number']::TEXT\[]);



A new task will be created in order to fix the main cause of this issue.

What’s the relationship between this item, MPDI-1629, and PAR-1466? Because MPDI items don’t need to be cloned and moved to PAR. They can be moved directly to PAR, without needing a clone. 

Also, I see the linked [https://sanmina.atlassian.net/browse/PAR-1466|https://sanmina.atlassian.net/browse/PAR-1466|smart-link] has “MES 15.62.5” in its name. I’m assuming that that is a typo meant to refer to 15.61.5? In which case, should this be part of 15.62? Or would it be better to assign it to the 15.61.2 sprint, which I believe is intended to serve as a bucket for any of these internal patches that haven’t gone to production.

column1: SR #4303555 - Snap shots cannot be deleted in mesweb portal
column37:
Hello Team,

We have received a SR#4303555 <[https://it.sanmina.com/HD/SR/Details/4303555|https://it.sanmina.com/HD/SR/Details/4303555]>
from K03 plant reported that they are unable to delete the snapshot from
the MESWEB.

*Technical Details:*
MESWEB Link: [https://k03-mesweb.42-q.com/|https://k03-mesweb.42-q.com/]
Snapshot name: TEST
Site: K03
Server/Database: corpmesr4.sanmina.com/mesr_k03
RDS: mesweb-rds.42-q.com

*Issue Description:* User tried to delete the snapshot, first it was
deleted from the portal successfully. But if we logout and login again the
application the snapshot was still showing.

1. The snapshot "TEST" was created.

!https://attachment.freshdesk.com/inline/attachment?token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJpZCI6MjkwMjAzMTQwNzMsImRvbWFpbiI6IjQycS5mcmVzaGRlc2suY29tIiwiYWNjb3VudF9pZCI6NTk3OTQxfQ.cuhiXIrcTXLen4b58WBBPMEM-ffB92fBKZLKrpFRGAs|thumbnail!

!https://attachment.freshdesk.com/inline/attachment?token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJpZCI6MjkwMjAzMTQwNzQsImRvbWFpbiI6IjQycS5mcmVzaGRlc2suY29tIiwiYWNjb3VudF9pZCI6NTk3OTQxfQ.Dqt8iYW94rfXvvpNZiwRlF1jY3z_y_t-pLgsm5ILSWM|thumbnail!

showing.

We have checked in the E80 production MESWEB the same issue happens but in
the UAT(gbs_test) the snapshot was removed successfully.

K03(Prod):
[https://drive.google.com/a/sanmina-sci.com/file/d/10yggJ5PZ7Kg1zsivT0hYyqiOxQbLZ6g3/view?usp=sharing|https://drive.google.com/a/sanmina-sci.com/file/d/10yggJ5PZ7Kg1zsivT0hYyqiOxQbLZ6g3/view?usp=sharing]

column266:
28/Nov/19 4:11 PM;557058:2a899724-d514-45d4-8f31-46d9181d6a69;Hello [~accountid:5ab5521333719f2a50171fb1]   



The report “Assembly Throughput Report” is calling next tables:
measurement.activity 	                106 GB
measurement.measurement 	7448 GB

If you notice the tables are very big, we can improve the performance with activity table, but at the moment we try to find
the information into measurement table we can not improve the performance because there is no index we can use.

Indexes:
"pk_measurement" PRIMARY KEY, btree (activity_key, sub_pm, test_count, pm_group_code_key, test_type_key, pm_group_test_count)
Foreign-key constraints:
"fk_measurement_limit" FOREIGN KEY (test_type_key, sub_pm, pm_group_code_key) REFERENCES limits(test_type_key, sub_pm, pm_group_code_key)

for the parameters that the plant is using the report is trying to return    *192043* rows.

I think is necessary include more filters to refine the search. Can you ask to the plant if is possible get more parameters?

Can you help to talk with the plant about this?

Thanks,

Felipe.
column267:
17/Dec/19 7:10 AM;557058:563ca2b2-06ae-4174-aaac-df8f41a36384;[~accountid:5a8ffcf35c7a2233512b2393]

column1: Conditioning not considering only latest
column37:
Hello team,

Could you please help to take a look into this issue? Seems that the system is using the same measkey for all the data collected in Conditioning, even if it passes more than once through the process, so when the unit arrives to Jumper Visual Check it's taking all the cells that failed, not just the ones in the last test:
BS67G17-000267-10, passed 3 times though COND, one passed all the cell, 2nd failed 2 and 3rd failed one:  (1=PASS,  0=FAIL)

1st PASS:

!https://attachment.freshdesk.com/inline/attachment?token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJpZCI6MjkwMTg3NjMwNjYsImRvbWFpbiI6IjQycS5mcmVzaGRlc2suY29tIiwiYWNjb3VudF9pZCI6NTk3OTQxfQ.kWq6ppIrGhKZdAbxXO6MNCd7lLSjbGhWqo2qW6VOISY|thumbnail!

2nd pass 2 failed:

!https://attachment.freshdesk.com/inline/attachment?token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJpZCI6MjkwMTg3NjMwNjQsImRvbWFpbiI6IjQycS5mcmVzaGRlc2suY29tIiwiYWNjb3VudF9pZCI6NTk3OTQxfQ.diwWflJvcR7TorwAmGTcR9vjgyWp3NEc2TpMr4HwgZI|thumbnail!

In 3rd pass, one passed, the 2nd not:

!https://attachment.freshdesk.com/inline/attachment?token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJpZCI6MjkwMTg3NjMwNjUsImRvbWFpbiI6IjQycS5mcmVzaGRlc2suY29tIiwiYWNjb3VudF9pZCI6NTk3OTQxfQ.afs_RgJ6kEQWsZIwIGtXHMNAhhhpDRPeOy4_Y4JcXxc|thumbnail!

The issue reported is that in Vision it validates both cells:

!https://attachment.freshdesk.com/inline/attachment?token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJpZCI6MjkwMTg3NjMwNjMsImRvbWFpbiI6IjQycS5mcmVzaGRlc2suY29tIiwiYWNjb3VudF9pZCI6NTk3OTQxfQ.GN7M5VarNkKKT0-BX1FUN1VQVA4-WMlSPxgKW-zhoLs|thumbnail!

Vision check users the function  beehive_get_latest_inspection_measurement_activity  that calls this one beehive_get_latest_measurement_activity

Part of the query:
mes_beus_sv=> select
vm.measkey,
vm.recipe_key,
vm.test_group_name as test_group,
vm.test_step_name as test_step,
replace(replace(replace(replace(vm.test_step_name,'FTP_', ''),'CJ_',''),'AVR_',''),'ENG_','') as test_step_name,
vm.reference_designator,
vm.measurement_comments as comment,
vm.test_step_value as text_value,
vm.activity_key
from
measurement.v_measkey_all_detail vm
where
measkey =
(select
max(a.activity_key)
from
mds.serial s
inner join mds.activity a on s.serial_key = a.serial_key and a.action+0 = 36
where

column283:
30/Apr/21 7:54 PM;5aa2720c1e5627213ac76db9;Hello team, [~accountid:5e1634015361330daaeb3fb2], [~accountid:557058:b8ddbaad-8642-47e4-899a-022637d322ec] 

Checking on this issue I could find this, as per the Services team this is not a new requirement due to this dates back to late 2017 where there was a global requirement for three processes to +only+ +*consider the latest*+ +date from each process,+ and that’s the expected behavior here. 

Those processes are:

1.- Cold Leak

2.- CPT

3.- Conditioning

For this case, the main issue reported was that the *Conditioning* wasn't considering only the latest date.



On that way, considering the latest example provided by the user 

Conditioning data is always only considering the last run.

 

So let’s take this example.

a)       *10/2/2019 8:37:40 PM* - There was a conditioning run that FAILED Cells 1 and 2.

!image-20210430-234529.png|width=2299,height=256!

b)    *10/10/2019 7:38:35 PM*  - It did a retest and FAILED Cells 1.

!image-20210430-234615.png|width=2299,height=256!

c)    At CPT it should record defects for Cell 1 (latest) and not Cell 1 and 2.

!image-20210430-234644.png|width=2299,height=256!

So, According to the customer, even for those defects recorded in *Conditioning* that were repaired in the same station,  the system should “reopen“ them,  and show up in Cell Jumper to be repaired again.

Could you please help us to understand if that’s the way the system works right now? 



Thanks in advance and regards.



Regards.

We are closing this Jira item according to the following comment:

We changed our minds according to the archiving/compress solution we developed some months ago. It did not achieve our expectations in terms of performance/memory consumption. So we decided to go forward with a PowerShell script which daily runs and remove the test files older than one week for the plants which have a high production volume. The script is already applied in the CORPMEASW03 server, that’s the reason we did not face any new occurrence so far. For the non-high production volume plants, the same script runs, but monthly.

column266:
01/Oct/19 12:43 PM;5a986673bfa99132b5b66f1a;This happens due to trying to constrain the Angular Material styles into the visible area of the Command Register and not have it “overflow” into the Portal as a whole. While this goal is nice, in order to have a consistent look and feel, the Angular Material team has put in a lot of work to ensure that all the component styles work as expected regardless of where they are used. 21/Aug/19 7:06 PM;557058:e985e556-7ff0-4bf4-a720-6e6d22712971;[~accountid:557058:bc8b9612-3abe-41a0-bfa7-f89f184be2bf] [~accountid:557058:4584bc53-9882-4708-a327-8299d61f108e] 



We have been discussing this with Robert and Keith, and doing some research.  On the Serial Input Line, both the Serial Build Mask (SERIAL=) and the Product Build  Mask (PRODUCT=)  should support multiple sets of substrings ( in \[x,y] format) to identify substrings of characters from the scanned serial number. 



John and I verified that the substrings applied for the part number on the serial number are on the input value, not after the serial build mask is applied.



And from the examples, both serial build mask and part build mask can have multiple sets of substrings to include in the new 'built' value.

column1: Nimesh stop issue
column37:
Fresh Desk Ticket # 1865

During nimesh stop, the system is moving the subkit before the payload is finish saving. BM66G12-1924-005.A.2

From logs, the Stop was at 7:02 am , but in the Unit History (and DB)  the serial passed to the next location at 05:50:


6/13/2019 4:59 AM MES Start BM66G12-1924-005.A.2 Status: \{"success":true,"message":"","data":\{"mesh_welding_disable":"0","press_disable":""}}. Total Sec: 9.440178

6/13/2019 7:02 AM MES Stop Advance BM66G12-1924-005.A.2 Status: \{"success":false,"message":"The tool <ANW-01> is not in use","data":\[]}. Total Records: 766. Total Sec: 10.686137



During nimesh stop when advance =true,

It supposed to take the measurement data and then advance the subkit.

It is advancing the subkit before the measurement is done so it gives a flow error back.

column1: AWSELB Cookie Issue
column37:
Freshdesk Ticket #1822


Hi Billy,

This issue is related to the 42Q portal slowness issue, which was “controlled” applying as workaround increasing the timeout for the (AWSELB) Cookie.

Please see below information as a summary of this problem:

–  –  – 
On Thursday, May 09 2019 some plants reported slowness in Data Collector portlet in production.42-q.com portal, and also the portlet keeps stuck.

The portal "production.42-q.com" generates a cookie in the Web browser called "AWSELB" which was getting hung even if expiration time was not reached yet, it caused the portlet "Data Collector" got frozen.


The expiration time for the (AWSELB) Cookie  was taken from 60 min to 24 hours and a day after it was changed to 7 days timeout.
–  –  – 
(See the below image for evidence of the mentioned cookie)

!2019-06-05.png|width=200,height=183!

 

Details:

* Related SRs:
4090724	E30 - Guadalajara
4090727	E34 - Guadalajara
4090750	K03 - Reynosa
4090900	E51 - Guadalajara
4098346	E83 - Penang
4103605	E79 - G China

Evidence:

[https://drive.google.com/drive/u/0/folders/1LLAGhkrUbBba_qQbackXPnzhLFIbNRS1|https://drive.google.com/drive/u/0/folders/1LLAGhkrUbBba_qQbackXPnzhLFIbNRS1]

We would like follow up this issue and obtain a permanent solution.
Let us know if you have any questions.

Regards.

column1: OEE Connections Issue (Corpmes8)
column37:
Freshdesk Ticket #1820

Hello Allen,



 Plant E34 started to use OEE and that causing huge increase in memory used by postgres individual process. Operative system detected danger and was terminating the process with most usage of RAM. Tomcat was killed as it uses more ram than each postgres individual process. Most impacted plants E34 Guad, E30 Guad and K03 Reynosa. 



Errors found:

corpmes8: /mes/mds/logs/mds.log



\[mes_e30_06:print_label_engine] \[2019-05-27 10:50:06.070] \[INFO] - connect: Connection refused

\[mes_e30_06:labeng] \[2019-05-27 10:50:06.072] \[ERROR] - Web Service Execution Error  





Error from the log viewer  :



\[07:39:39,184] \[WARN] - Instance ID -1 is not present in the available list of instances. K88_01 - Penang, Malaysia (corpmeasw03.sanmina.com).

\[07:46:21,242] \[WARN] - Instance ID -1 is not present in the available list of instances. K88_01 - Penang, Malaysia (corpmeasw03.sanmina.com).

\[07:55:40,362] \[WARN] - Instance ID -1 is not present in the available list of instances. E04_01 - Manchester, USA (corpmeasw03.sanmina.com)

DBA team identified conduit does not close postgres connections



corpmes8:/var/lib/pgsql>> ps aux | grep idle | awk '\{mem\[$12]+=int($6/1024)}; \{cpuper\[$12]+=$3};\{memper\[$12]+=$4};\{con\[$12]+=1}; END \{for (i in mem) \{print cpuper\[i]"% ",memper\[i]"% ",mem\[i]" MB ",i, con\[i]}}' | sort -k3nr 

14.4%  52.9%  40417 MB  mds 195

0%  4.8%  3730 MB  usr_spc 25

29.8%  3%  2285 MB  conduit 13

0.2%  0.5%  450 MB  measurement 9

0%  0%  6 MB  mds_rdr 1

0%  0%  6 MB  mds_rdr_e30 1

0%  0%  4 MB  audit_e30_05_ro 1



Postgres consumed 237 * 100MB + 10GB (shared_buffers) + 512MB + ...

more connection then more memory.. 

Server corpmes 8 was rebooted 2 times, one to restore some hung processes and release resources. The second reboot was to apply some config changes and double the RAM memory.

Since the connectivity between MES was lost with measurement, user was not able to process measurement  files until meas service was restarted.

Some indexes were added to measurement tables that use OEE information.  Could you please confirm if this is the permanent solution?

Also as a workaround there is an script in place that runs every 2 minutes and terminates Conduit connections that are idle for 30 minutes or more and only for mes_e34_01 in corpmes8. 

If you need more information about it, please let me know it. 

Regards.

 On Tue, Mar 19, 2019 at 8:08 PM Samuel Rico <samuel.rico@42-q.com> wrote: 
 
 
      
 HI team, 
 We have replicated this issue and found that we have the same problem on Medical Production,  
   
 
 Issue: No able to export Masurement data (From Unit history) Medical Environment 
 Application: Mesweb, report Unit history  
 Error : Could not get Measurement Data 
 ERROR Report:453 - Error in formatMeasurement trying to get json 
 java.net.ConnectException: Connection refused 
   
 
   
   
 
 
 portal: medical.42-q.com
 
 
 Mesweb Server: corpmedmesweb.42-q.com (10.180.8.38) 
 Domain tested: e73-mesweb-med.42-q.com
 
 
 
   
 From the Medical Production, we found that there was the same issue when we executed the call to export the measurement data on the same server. 
   
  
 Tring to call the measurement info to export from the server itself: 
 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
 
 [samuel_rico@corpmedrpt tmp]$ wget "http://e73-mesweb-med.42-q.com/Sanm.MESWeb.Measurement.WS/service/measurementlotsection?projectId=1&activities=[2046412907,2074958023]&datasourceId=151" 
 --2019-03-19 16:30:27--  http://e73-mesweb-med.42-q.com/Sanm.MESWeb.Measurement.WS/service/measurementlotsection?projectId=1&activities=[2046412907,2074958023]&datasourceId=151
 
 Resolving e73-mesweb-med.42-q.com... 10.180.8.38
 
 Connecting to e73-mesweb-med.42-q.com|10.180.8.38|:80... failed: Connection refused.
 
   
   
  From the Web, we found the Measurement data could not see on the Unit history, but it appears in the exported data:  
 
  
 
 
 
 
 
 
   
   
 portal: medval.42-q.com
 
  
 
 Mesweb server: cirrusmedrpt1.42-q.com (10.180.11.183) 
 Mesweb domain tested: e73-mesweb-med-uat.42-q.com 
   
   
 
 From the Medical Production, we found that there was the same issue when we executed the call to export the measurement data on the same server. 
   
  
 Tring to call the measurement info to export from the server itself: 
 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
  
 
 [samuel_rico@cirrusmedrpt1 tmp]$ wget "http://e73-mesweb-med-uat.42-q.com/Sanm.MESWeb.Measurement.WS/service/measurementlotsection?projectId=1&activities=[2046412907,2074958023]&datasourceId=151" 
 --2019-03-19 17:56:04--  http://e73-mesweb-med-uat.42-q.com/Sanm.MESWeb.Measurement.WS/service/measurementlotsection?projectId=1&activities=[2046412907,2074958023]&datasourceId=151 
 Resolving e73-mesweb-med-uat.42-q.com... 10.180.11.183 
 Connecting to e73-mesweb-med-uat.42-q.com|10.180.11.183|:80... failed: Connection refused. 
 
   
 From the Web, we found the Measurement data could not see on the Unit history, and also does not appear  in the exported data: 
   
 
 
 
 
 
 
   
   
   
 Solution: 
 The mesweb team found that the issue is caused due the String call is taking as defauld the port "80" to connect to the application mesweb, so we tried to export using the port "8080" to connect in the own server. 
 This solution requires a code change, so it will be discussed with the team to apply it as proper.

column1: 4007117 - Sha2 Site: Can not expend the Measurement Data of unit history
column37:
Hi Jimena,

S18 reported they have problem to view measurement data in unit history report.

MES Web Site:  http://mesweb.s18.sanmina.com/Default.aspx
MES Web server: SHA2APMESW01
Serial Number:  05417627001F60723  -   05417627001F60730

If they click "view measurement data" in process "Functional Test 1", the measurement date in process "Assembly verify 1" will be opened.
Plant couldn't see the measurement data in process "Functional Test 1".

There was an issue with this mesweb on Feb 19th.
The error is "Config Error, There is a duplicate 'system.web.extensions/scripting/scriptResourceHandler' section defined"
I Removed the duplicated section settings in file H:\Apps\MESWeb2\Execution\Web\web.config then mesweb can be opened without error.
(backup the original file to web_bk.config)
I am not sure if it matters.

Could you please help to have a look on it? Thanks in advance.

column1: 4001461 - Assembly by Location - OPTIONS ASM_BY_PROCNAME=NO
column37:
Freshdesk Ticket #1253
 Hi 42Q Support Team,

Please find the subjected problem description, where the user from the E59
plant configured two assemblies for two different locations for the same
process in 42Q. However, on the SDE they configured *"OPTIONS
ASM_BY_PROCNAME=NO" *in order to get the unit processed based on the
location.

But still while processing on the second assembly location it kept
prompting the first assembly configuration rather than the second assembly
setup. Let us explain in detail with the scenario's tested from our end.

*Details.:*

Portal.: https://portal-uat.42-q.com
Site.: GBS_TEST
MES Server.: corpuat1.sanmina.com
MES DB.: mes_gbs_test

Route name: H Assembly Test Route

Part No: HASSEMBLYTEST
Serial No: HAST(6)n
Station ID: ASSEMBLY TEST

[image: image.png]

[image: image.png]

*Scenario 1.:*

OPTIONS ROUTE_BY_PROCNAME=YES
OPTIONS ASM_BY_PROCNAME=NO

Please find the SN# HAST000014, scanned and using "MOVE" command it was
moved to the location *"HAS1" *in order add the component from this
location. On *"HAS1" *location the Non-Tracked component added with the ref
designator - CMP1 successfully and from there it was "MOVE" to *HAS2 *in
order to add the second non-tracked component with different assembly setup.

[image: image.png]

[image: image.png]

Thought the assembly configured for the location *"HAS2" *still it did not
prompt for the assembly in order to add the component against the
respective serial number.

[image: image.png]

*Scenario 2.:*

*P*lease find the *SN# HAST000017, *where the serial passed to a
location *"HAS2"
*in order to add the configured second assembly non-tracked component.

[image: image.png]

SFDCIII=# select * from assembly where "location-key"='506';
 part-key | location-key | step | comp_part_mask | ref_designator |
comp_id_mask  |              comp_id_prompt               | component_type |
 comp_loc-key | process_name | assembly-key
----------+--------------+------+----------------+----------------+---------------+-------------------------------------------+----------------+
--------------+--------------+--------------
     1222 |          506 |   10 |                | CMP2           |
*ASSEMBLY2(3)n* | *Assembly of 503 DC: (MASK: ASSEMBLY2(3)n)* | 0
    |
            0 | H Assembly   |           85
(1 row)

At this location, the configured assembly prompt is different but still, it
prompts the first assembly *"HAS1"* pattern mask due to the same process
name. Hence, the option *ASM_BY_PROCNAME=NO *not working even though if the
assembly component is being added based on the locations.

[image: image.png]

*Scenario 3.:*

OPTIONS ROUTE_BY_PROCNAME=NO
OPTIONS ASM_BY_PROCNAME=NO

After changing the above option in SDE, scanned the same serial number
- *HAST000017
on "HAS2" (Second Assembly)* where it prompted the correct component mask
which was configured in assembly.

[image: image.png]

[image: image.png]
Would you mind to check with the developer any other method of scanning two
different locations with two different assemblies for the same process in
42Q? Because the plant wants to use if for the reporting purpose in order
to get the Yield data easily.

*Note.: *At this moment, as a workaround solution plant created a different
process name for *HAS1 and HAS2* in order to get the two different
assemblies scanned on two different locations.


Regards,
Aravamudhan. R

--

to download it to SFDC PC:10.180.8.31, and it was failed and prompted

process at route".Then I found the route created yesterday had an issue and
the test result is not right.

Today I configure the route: H Assembly Test Route again, it is
*HPRE-->HASS->COMP
*and download it to SFDC PC successfully.

The *HASS* location is logistic location, and it has two physical
locations: HAS1 and HAS2. Although HAS1 and HAS2 have the same process but
different components, then they will prompt different components when
scanning an S/N at HAS1 or HAS2 location according to the Options set up on

reported to Gary and he will assign the code check. Thanks!

Christy

Carlos Romero via sanmina.com   4:40 AM (5 hours ago)     to Luis, Israel, Pedro, Raihan, Mohd, Venugopal, Waseem, Shivaji, Robert, Bernard, Checky, Grace, Javier, Cristine, Gordon, Jill, Adan, Roberto, Luis, Rituraj, Eduardo, Juan, Emmanuel, Fabiola, Sunny, Naresh, Lie, Al, Mike, Fabio, MES, Sriram                 To all IPMs, This note is to inform you that given the recent problems faced by multiple plants with the reporting tool our management has decided to roll back non-medical MESWeb to the previous version. column277:
14/Feb/19 5:42 PM;5ab5521333719f2a50171fb1;Note added by Elena Romero [42-Q] in Freshdesk:
 The heap memory in the HA servers increased causing the servers to slow down the performance. This was caused by 94 schedules wrongly configured by users and not even running, the schedules were disabled and the server heap memory was recovered for some time, however the issues persisted. MESWEB team will be working on a way to identify those schedules and monitor the schedules quantity in order to identify further issues on time.     After that a roll back of the last features in February non-medical upgrade was required to mitigate this issue     Also 2+  HA instances were created in order to improve mesweb performances, right now we have 4 instances running.     Finally after all these improvements mesweb has been working properly.

We are closing this ticket for now, feel free to contact us if any other assistance is needed. column1: Lutron - KV Control: Missing supply_locator - Shop Order 13809398
column37:
Freshdesk Ticket #1202
 Please process this 42Q Support Ticket for Lutron Brookdale.


*Background:*
Customer ERP (E1) generates .csv Work Order file. File is transferred to
42Q provided SFTP. 42Q retrieves file every 15 min and processes the WO
Create web service to generate the Shop Order with Parts List (Shop Order
BOM/Recipe) for traceability purposes in Kit Verify (KV Control). The Work
Order File contains all information necessary to create the Shop Order as
well as BOM for said order. The supply_locator is provided in the file, as
well as created in the BOM to display during Kit Consolidation (KV Control).


*Prerequisites:*
Work Order .csv file contains necessary Parts List information to create
the Shop Order
supply_locator information provided in Work Order .csv file for (Component)
Part Number

Example Component Part Number in .csv file:
50,699100,PartDescription,1.0000,1.0,REFDES,*LOCATOR*,PUSH,Insert

Shop Order is Released
Location Type=KITTING_CONSOLIDATION defined in Route, and Route assigned to
Shop Order Part Number
(Component) Part Number KV Controlled=true
Attribute Definition created and Released=true for (component) Part Number
at the Process assigned to the Kitting Location

Note: all prerequisites met for Shop Order in question.


*Problem:*
Supply Locator (supply_locator) did not display in KV Control form for any
of the component part numbers


*Details:*
UAT URL: https://uatportal.42-q.com/web/42q_lutron_br1
Shop Order: 13809398
Work Order File Name: WO13809398_190204141213.csv (attached)

column286:
19/Aug/19 9:28 AM;557058:0794a087-3aea-4fdf-8299-388e6e778dd0;Hi Juan, 

I took a look in the unit history of the CM66G14-017287-22, and I saw that the unit was moved to PCMV but it was scanned in the ADMN Administrator location. That’s why the unit is not going to P: Stack Mongoose.

column1: Wrong table structure
column37:
Hi team.

Lutron is facing an issue with schedules, it is caused because of a record trying to be stored in the incorrect order by MESWeb application. The fastest way to fix it is by replacing the table with the fields in the correct order.

Server: 42qmesuat2.42-q.com
Database: mesweb_central

Can you please help me to drop the "jobs" table in mesweb_central and create it again as follows:

DROP TABLE central.jobs;
CREATE TABLE central.jobs
(
  id integer NOT NULL DEFAULT nextval('jobs_id_seq'::regclass),
  name text NOT NULL,
  enabled boolean NOT NULL,
  description text NOT NULL,
  created timestamp with time zone NOT NULL,
  snapshotid integer NOT NULL,
  configuration bytea,
  CONSTRAINT jobs_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id),
  CONSTRAINT jobs_snapshotid_fkey FOREIGN KEY (snapshotid)
      REFERENCES central.snapshots (id) MATCH SIMPLE
      ON UPDATE NO ACTION ON DELETE NO ACTION
)
WITH (
  OIDS=FALSE
);

It is a UAT environment and the table has no records on it.

Regards

column1: Monocle function not working.
column37:
Freshdesk Ticket #808
 Hello Team,

Information:

mes_db: mes_e34_01
server: corpmes8.sanmina.com
mesr server: corpmesr4.sanmina,com
portal link: production.42-q.com
SR Related: https://it.sanmina.com/HD/SR/Details/3909495

The plant is reporting problems with the positions in Monocle of the MFG
Lines, when they change position in X and Y, the position in not updated in
monocle. This is affecting all the mes_db from the plant mes_e34_01,
mes_e34_02, mes_e34_03, mes_e34_04, mes_e34_05, mes_e34_05 and mes_e34_07

The user provide us this MFG Line to check "M108_EOLA_TESLA".

Now the MFG Line is in 1560 in position X and 352 in position Y.

mes_e34_01=> select * from mfg_line where name='M108_EOLA_TESLA';
 mfg_line_key |      name       | description  | pixel_x | pixel_y |
man_power | work_hour | min_sample_size | wip_mfg_line |  site_id
--------------+-----------------+--------------+---------+---------+-----------+-----------+-----------------+--------------+------------
           15 | M108_EOLA_TESLA | EOL AUT TEST |    1560 |     352 |
 1 |         8 |               1 | f            | E34_GDL_P3
(1 row)

Also in corpmesr4 has the same information X=1560 anf Y=352

mesr_e34=> select * from mfg_line where name='M108_EOLA_TESLA';
 mfg_line_key |      name       | description  | pixel_x | pixel_y |
man_power | work_hour | min_sample_size | wip_mfg_line |  site_id
--------------+-----------------+--------------+---------+---------+-----------+-----------+-----------------+--------------+------------
           15 | M108_EOLA_TESLA | EOL AUT TEST |    1560 |     352 |
 1 |         8 |               1 | f            | E34_GDL_P3
(1 row)

In the table monocle_info we can see the information X=1560 anf Y=352 and
this is the information that will be shown in Monocle


[image: image.png]

We applied a change in X position X=1565

mes_e34_01=> select * from mfg_line where name='M108_EOLA_TESLA';
 mfg_line_key |      name       | description  | pixel_x | pixel_y |
man_power | work_hour | min_sample_size | wip_mfg_line |  site_id
--------------+-----------------+--------------+---------+---------+-----------+-----------+-----------------+--------------+------------
           15 | M108_EOLA_TESLA | EOL AUT TEST |    1565 |     352 |
 1 |         8 |               1 | f            | E34_GDL_P3
(1 row)

Checking the mesr server the information was replicated without problem

mesr_e34=> select * from mfg_line where name='M108_EOLA_TESLA';
 mfg_line_key |      name       | description  | pixel_x | pixel_y |
man_power | work_hour | min_sample_size | wip_mfg_line |  site_id
--------------+-----------------+--------------+---------+---------+-----------+-----------+-----------------+--------------+------------
           15 | M108_EOLA_TESLA | EOL AUT TEST |    1565 |     352 |
 1 |         8 |               1 | f            | E34_GDL_P3
(1 row)


But the information in monocle_info is not updated we still seeing the
previous configuration X=1560 and Y=352.

[image: image.png]


But we need run the function manually to see the information updated in
monocle_info table

mesr_e34=# select * from soms.update_monocle();
 update_monocle
----------------

(1 row)

The information is updated after the function runs

[image: image.png]


Could you create the JIRA for MESWeb Team for this issue?

Regards.

--

To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to supportgroup.42-q+unsubscribe@42-q.com.

column1: SR#3904067 # Measurement activity monitor# autorefresh#Browser Hung
column37:
Freshdesk Ticket #801
 Hi Support,

We have an issue SR#3904067 with Measurement where if the autorefresh is
set, then the browser get hung after a while. We have high cpu and memory
utilization when this runs.

This issue occurs only for the measurement core version >3.1 (i.e
integrated to the portal).
If we test the same using direct measurement url then autorefresh works
fine.

Could you pls check with Measurement team?

Plant: E90
 Search parameters - Top Record: 5| Refresh Rate: 5
Portal: medical.42-q.com/web/mes_e90_m01/measurement-operation
Direct url: meas02.sanmina.com

column1: E61 - 3874424 - "Huawei Invoicing" report issues
column37:
Freshdesk Ticket #623
 Hello 42Q Support Team,

Please find the subjected SR# problem, where the report *"Huawei Invoicing"*
was developed to populate the information with the invoice details which
are being shipped to the customer.

Here in this report the field "Item Code" displays the part number by
trimming the last two characters *"MR"* from the right side of the part
number. At this moment, from the below query highlight parameter
eliminating the character "M" & "R" from the right due to which the
expected part number not getting displayed on the report.

*Details.:*

*MESR Server.: corpmesr4*
*MESR DB.: mesr_e61*
*Report Name.: Huawei Invoicing*

*Example.:*

Original Part Number.: *03021LRRMR*
Expected Output PN.: *03021LRR*

mesr_e61=# select part_number from part where part_number like '%LRRMR';
 part_number
-------------
 03021LRRMR
(1 row)

mesr_e61=# select rtrim('03021LRRMR','MR');
 rtrim
--------
 03021L  *-------------------------- Here is the problem and this output to
be modified on the developed query -----------------------------*
(1 row)



*Report Query.:*

select distinct s.serial_number,*rtrim(part_number, 'MR')* as "Item_Code",
coalesce((select attr_data from attribute at where  at.serial_key =
s.serial_key and at.source_key = s.source_key and at.attr_name_key =
   (select attr_name_key from attr_name atr where name = 'Third Party
Repairs' and at.source_key = atr.source_key and removed = 0)),'') "Looper" ,
 p.description,
coalesce((select attr_data from attribute at where  at.serial_key =
s.serial_key and at.source_key = s.source_key and at.attr_name_key =
   (select attr_name_key from attr_name atr where name = 'Shipping
Reference' and at.source_key = atr.source_key and removed = 0)),'') as
"Shipping_Reference",
coalesce(ud.repair_conclusion,'') as "Repair_Conclusion",
coalesce((select attr_data from attribute at where  at.serial_key =
s.serial_key and at.source_key = s.source_key and at.attr_name_key =
   (select attr_name_key from attr_name atr where name = 'DA Service Type'
and at.source_key = atr.source_key and removed = 0)),'') as
"DA_Service_Type",
coalesce(ud.failure_reason,'') as "Defect_Code",
coalesce(to_char(s.complete_ts,'YYYY-MM-DD'),'') as "Date"
 --,s.serial_key
from rto.pg_4_lrs_unit_defect ud
inner join serial s on s.serial_number = ud.serial_number
inner join activity a on a.serial_key = s.serial_key and a.source_key =
s.source_key
inner join part p on p.part_key = s.part_key and p.source_key = s.source_key
inner join customer_part cp on cp.part_key = p.part_key and cp.source_key =
p.source_key
inner join customer c on c.customer_key = cp.customer_key
where a.ts between <%Start%> and <%End%>
and customer_name = 'Huawei'
and a1='COMP '

*Note.: *We have part numbers consists *.MR as well, *so while modifying
the query please be specific to remove even "*.MR" & "MR" *in order to
display the exact item (PN) to display on the report.

mesr_e61=# select part_number from part where part_number like '%.MR' order
by part_key desc limit 10;
 part_number
-------------
 03020RAR*.MR*
 52450607.MR
 02238806.MR
 02317151.MR
 03030LNB.MR
 02239582.MR
 03053558.MR
 03020XGR.MR
 02317165.MR
 02317164.MR
(10 rows)

mesr_e61=# select part_number from part where part_number like '%MR' order
by part_key desc limit 10;
 part_number
-------------
 03030DQU*MR*
 03020SBEMR
 03053947MR
 03054153MR
 03030HNKMR
 03039040MR
 03030CDLMR
 03020MLGMR
 03020SJSMR
 02310UKSMR
(10 rows)

Regards,
Aravamudhan. R

column1: 3858646 - Mesweb scheduled report name issue
column37:
Freshdesk Ticket #531
 Hi, 42Q Support Team,

We received a complaint from EMEA region, where the user scheduled a
snapshot with the file name as "*CZ_BOARDS_FORECAST<%date%>*" under the
configuration in order to receive the file with the file name along with
the generating date of the report i.e., if the file is scheduled for today
then it should be  "*CZ_BOARDS_FORECAST20181009".*

However, this conversion is being executed only on the folder level whereas
the same not happening with the file on how the report is being scheduled.
So while discussing with the user, stated this is something like a bug
where it required code change on the core level.

Hence we request you to check and take this problem to the concern team and
help to apply the fix during this month Non-Medical Upgrade and do the
needful. Since this report is being sent to the customer as they are
receiving the file without the proper file name and could not identify the
date.

*Details.:*

*MESWEB URL.: **https://zebra-mesweb.42-q.com/
<https://zebra-mesweb.42-q.com/>*
*Snapshot Name.: CZ_Daily Boards Forecast Report*
*File Name.: CZ_BOARDS_FORECAST<%date%>*

*Note.: Not only this <date> parameter, even facing the same problem with
the below listed parameters as well.*










*<%datetime%><%date%><%time%><%YYYY%><%MM%>"<%DD%>"<%hh%>"<%mm%>"<%ss%>"*





Regards,
Aravamudhan. R

column1: E38# Serials activity.location key updated as non-route location even if we have multipass
column37:
Freshdesk Ticket #458
 Hi Support,

E38 reported an SR#3830846 where the activity records are updating for
non-route locations even if we have multipassed the locations in route.
This only happens in 42q but user have records where it works fine in
legacy.

Serial: 6S152309707 ---- Processed in 2015
Scanned location: S437
Device number= 437
Serial current location: BTPT
Location BTPT is multipassed with 437

Correct Activity records in terms of location in legacy,
[image: image.png]


After migrating to 42Q. The same kind of scenario executed on the same
location

Serial: 6S170102151  --- Processed now in 42q
Scanned location: S437
Device number= 437
Serial current location: BTPT
Location BTPT is multipassed with 437

[image: image.png]

Reason why plant wanted this to be same like legacy is they are using the
command !!1BACK2WIP2 which moves the unit to the location where it was
moved previous to non online status like 28,29,30.

Can we get Dave/Gary advice on this?

--

column277:
22/Oct/18 4:45 PM;5ab5521333719f2a50171fb1;Note added by Dave Plasterer in Freshdesk:
 The issue here seems to be that the move2hold command uses the location
where the command is scanned as the location where the activity occurs.
Legacy used the serial.location_key as the location where the activity
occurs.
That is true for both !!1 and !!2 executions.

You can assign a jira task to Christina, but it will likely be some time
before it could be updated, validated and deployed.

Thanks.

column1: E60 - 3848229 - WIP Serial in shop order report export failed
column37:
Freshdesk Ticket #434
 Hi 42Q Support Team,

Please find the below screenshot, where the E60 plant unable to export the
data from the report "WIP serials in shop order" whereas for the other
reports we are able to export it without any problem.

We simulated the problem in the UAT environment, where it works fine but
there was a change on the query between UAT and Production. However, while
checking it from the Kibana log found with an error as *"Time writing file
on short (elapsed time) =300"*

Hence we request you to take this case further to the developer and help to
fix this problem and do the needful. In case if you need any further
assistance on this problem please do let us know.

*Details.:*

*Portal.: **https://production.42-q.com <https://production.42-q.com>*
*Server.: corpmes4.sanmina.com <http://corpmes4.sanmina.com>*
*MES DB.: mes_e60_01*
*MESR Server.: corpmesr6.sanmina.com <http://corpmesr6.sanmina.com>*
*MESR DB.: mesr_e60*
*Report Name.: WIP serials in shop order*



*Query Used in Production.:*

select so.shop_order_number as "JOB_NUMBER", s.serial_number as
"SERIAL_NUMBER", l.long_workstation as "LOCATION", s.quantity as
"QUANTITY", to_char(s.loc_ts,'FMmm/FMdd/YYYY HH12:MI:SS AM') as
"LAST_SCAN_DATE"
from serial_iswip s
left join shop_order so on s.shop_order_key = so.shop_order_key and
s.source_key=so.source_key
left join location l on s.location_key = l.location_key and
s.source_key=l.source_key
where s.unit_status_key >= 15 and s.unit_status_key < 30

*Query Used in UAT.:*

select so.shop_order_number as "JOB_NUMBER", s.serial_number as
"SERIAL_NUMBER", l.long_workstation as "LOCATION", s.quantity as
"QUANTITY", to_char(s.loc_ts,'FMmm/FMdd/YYYY HH12:MI:SS AM') as
"LAST_SCAN_DATE"
from serial s
left join shop_order so on s.shop_order_key = so.shop_order_key and
s.source_key=so.source_key
left join location l on s.location_key = l.location_key and
s.source_key=l.source_key
where s.unit_status_key >= 15 and s.unit_status_key < 30

*Kibana Logs.:*

column1: E73 (Medical) - From the "My Assigned" module once the calibration status changed the same changes not getting updated on the CMMS Asset --> Asset --> Calibration (Tab)
column37:
Hello Barry Zhao,

Details.:

Portal.: http://medval.42-q.com
Server.: corpmedptsuat1.42-q.com

Issue 4.: The user creating an asset with the calibration required as "YES" with the calibration status as "In Use" from the Asset --> Calibration (Tab). Later the user from the Production --> CMMS Calibration --> My Assigned module on the respective created Asset, due to some reason the user trying to change the calibration status from "In Use" to "On Hold" or "Scrap" or "Lost" etc., and then saved the changes. Even after saved, the changed status not getting updated on the Asset level i.e., on the CMMS Asset --> Asset ID --> Calibration (Tab) and remains with the same status as "In Use".

Please find the below snap, where from Shop Floor Control --> Configuration --> CMMS Asset --> Asset new Asset ID# ARAV110890 was created and on the Calibration (Tab) with Calibration Needed mark as "YES" along with the status as "In Use".

Later, on the Production --> CMMS Calibration --> My Assigned the user was trying to change the respective asset calibration status from "In Use" to "On Hold" for some reason and then tried to save the changes and it was saved successfully.

After changing the status the same not getting updated automatically on the respective Asset --> Calibration (Tab) which is causing the problem with the calibration process. We request you to check the same problem from your end and help to fix it ASAP.

 !image-2018-08-22-18-23-32-765.png|thumbnail!  !image-2018-08-22-18-27-41-069.png|thumbnail!

column1: SR# 3800681 Material on Board report didn't fetch correct data from Rework Report
column37:
Freshdesk Ticket #221
 Hello support team,


E81 user reported the Material on Board report has some issue.

Firstly from Rework report, the board-barcode: P18302028 has updated a new
metarial barcode:
E81013815773-0522




However, at Material on Board report, the component barcode didnot update /
appear to the new material barcode:




From PTSR_E81:
select * from component_1 where barcode in
('E81013815773-0515','E81013815773-0522')
component_id |barcode           |
-------------|------------------|
14843141     |E81013815773-0515 |
14843190     |E81013815773-0522 |


The Material on Board report was from function "rpt_material_on_board" in
PTSR_E81 db. After I analysed this function code with dba, we found some
issue below:

When I ran this queue under PTSR_E81, there was no result appeared,
barcode  *E81013815773-0522 was not available.*

*select  distinct 'PTS' datasource, s.barcode pcbid,
dateadd('ss',s.scan_time,'1970-01-01')::text scan_time, p.is_2nd_side ::
varchar side, p.designator, t.tooling_name feeder ,*
*st.station_name station, ws.ws_name workstation, '' machincetype ,''
flexa_Job*
*,dateadd('ss',lc.up_time,'1970-01-01')::text
up_time,dateadd('ss',lc.down_time,'1970-01-01')::text down_time,*
*lc.component_id*
*from (*
*select s.barcode,s.scan_time,abs(s.ws_id) as
ws_id,lcb.load_component_id,pick_list_id *
*from scanning_1 s, scan_comp_batch scb, load_comp_batch lcb*
*where  scb.batch_id = lcb.batch_id and  s.scanning_id=scb.scanning_id and
s.barcode= 'P18302028'*
*) s,load_component_1 lc ,pick_list_item p, work_station ws, station st,
tooling t*
*where s.load_component_id=lc.load_component_id*
*and s.ws_id = ws.ws_id   --and lc.ws_id=ws.ws_id*
*and lc.station_id=st.station_id*
*and lc.tooling_id = t.tooling_id --and s.barcode= v_board_barcode*
*and s.pick_list_id=p.pick_list_id *
*AND ((p.is_2nd_side in (0,2) and s.ws_id = lc.ws_id) OR (p.is_2nd_side in
(1,2) and s.ws_id = -lc.ws_id))*
*AND lc.station_id=p.station_id *
*and lc.component_id = 14843190    --------  14843190 is component id of
barcode: E81013815773-0522  *


If searching *component_id = 14843141 *(component id of  E81013815773-0515),
I could have correct data.


Hence we presume the function code of  rpt_material_on_board might have to
analyse and modify.


Thank you and regards.
-- 

Best Regards

*Jeremy Jiang*

*MES Support Team*
*jeremy.jiang@42Q.com <jeremy.jiang@sanmina.com>*

--
