For this specific monitor, we have manually updated the data to make it work.        Regards,  Jasmine Ticket: https://42q.freshdesk.com/helpdesk/tickets/157
column269:
26/Jul/18 4:06 AM;5ab5521333719f2a50171fb1;Note added by Jasmine Zhu in Freshdesk:
 The issue is caused by SPC logic bug.     The last_group_time for this monitor is 1532278184,spc will check the following 8 hours from that time, it will collect data and transferred to spc if attributes larger than 5, we could see during the next 8 hours, there are only 4 add attributes  action(action=32),so spc will stuck here      mes_e81_01=> SELECT * FROM mds.activity WHERE 1=1 AND mes_e81_01->     ts > to_timestamp(1532278184  ) mes_e81_01->     AND ts <= to_timestamp(1532278184+3600*8) mes_e81_01->     AND part_key IN ( SELECT part_key FROM mds.part WHERE part_number='LFGUSP075804-200' ) mes_e81_01->     AND location_key in ( SELECT location_key FROM mds.location mes_e81_01(>     WHERE process_key IN ( SELECT process_key FROM mds.process WHERE process_name='Paste High BOT') mes_e81_01(>     AND sfdc_key IN ( SELECT sfdc_key FROM mds.sfdc_setup WHERE sfdc_id='p5523dc1' )); activity_key | serial_key | employee_key | location_key | action | pass_fail_seq | i1 | i2 |             a1             |  a2   |           ts           | part_key | quantity --------------+------------+--------------+--------------+--------+---------------+----+----+----------------------------+-------+------------------------+----------+---------- 629923965 |   82028098 |        48965 |          236 |     32 |             0 |  1 |  0 | Solder_Paste|Paste_High_B1 | 0.143 | 2018-07-23 08:49:37+08 |    49344 |         629923966 |   82028098 |        48965 |          236 |     32 |             0 |  2 |  0 | Solder_Paste|Paste_High_B2 | 0.132 | 2018-07-23 08:49:38+08 |    49344 |         629923970 |   82028098 |        48965 |          236 |     32 |             0 |  3 |  0 | Solder_Paste|Paste_High_B3 | 0.146 | 2018-07-23 08:49:39+08 |    49344 |         629923973 |   82028098 |        48965 |          236 |     32 |             0 |  4 |  0 | Solder_Paste|Paste_High_B4 | 0.152 | 2018-07-23 08:49:40+08 |    49344 |         (4 rows)     In order to fix it temporarily, developer manually update the last_group_time to the following 8 hours first action time,which is 2018-07-23 08:49:37+08, it is 1532306977  mes_e81_01=> select to_timestamp(1532306977); to_timestamp       ------------------------ 2018-07-23 08:49:37+08 (1 row)     Then it is working.

column1: CMMS Medical (UAT) - Scheduled PM Not Generating the WO automatically and not sending the E-Mail Alert
column37:
Hello Oliver Meng,

As same as the Non-Medical, two days back from E90 plant reported, that they have scheduled a PM (Preventive Maintenance) alert for every day which will remind the respective "Assigned Group" via an automatic email alert. But this automatic email alert is not working properly as expected where if we create the WO manually the configured group users are able to receive the mail.

Till yesterday we suspect that the problem is on the configured cronjobs but today with the help of Unix Team (Simon Jong) the problem has been rectified and added all the cronjobs to the Postgres and now the jobs were running good but on the logs folder /var/www/logs the logs are not getting updated.

Would you please help to check and let us know whether do we need to upgrade the CMMS Web Service to the latest as how we did for the Non-Medical (portal-uat.42-q.com) and do the needful.

Details.:

Portal.: medval.42-q.com
Server.: corpmedptsuat1.42-q.com
Database.: cmms

column1: SR#3514963-Slowness response for Production.42-q (Route Functionality)
column37:
*SR Description:*
We found slowness response on Production.42-q at below page
1. Shop Floor Control -> Configuration -> SFDC Configuration -> List Route -> Edit Route
2. Shop Floor Control -> Configuration -> SFDC Configuration -> Part x Route Assignment List undefined page
I compared response between Production.42-q and corpmesprtl3 then found the Production.42-q slower than corpmesprtl3.

1. I click edit on this route  Shop Floor ID: p5546dc1c  Route Name "FLOW#LFHNEE001144-01" it take more than 24 sec per response on Production.42-q  for 3 sec per response on Corpmesprtl3
2. more than 50 sec per response to select select route at "Part x Route Assignment Form undefined" page on Production.42-q for 2-3 sec per response on Corpmesprtl3

MDS server: corpmes3.sanmina.com
MDS database: mes_e91_01_1501

http://corpmesprtl3.sanmina.com/web/mes_e91_01_1501/sfdc-configuration
http://production.42-q.com/web/mes_e91_01_1501/sfdc-configuration

Please see more detail as the attached. Please fix it.
=======================================
*Email from Ramesh Pichaimuthu*
from: Ramesh Pichaimuthu [42-Q] <ramesh.pichaimuthu@42-q.com>
to: Billy <billy.huang@sanmina.com>,Fabio Pelissoni <fabio.pelissoni@sanmina-sci.com>,
cesar conde <cesar.conde@sanmina.com>, MES Support <mes.support@sanmina.com>
date:	Thu, Sep 28, 2017 at 5:12 AM
subject:	HA Slowness Compare to corpmesprtl3

Hi Billy,

We have an [SR#3514963|https://it.sanmina.com/HD/SR/Details/3514963] from E91 user about the slowness in HA when compare to corpmesprtl3. We have duplicated the issue and yes there is some slowness.

Test:
Server: corpmes3/mes_e91_01

Route name: COM#AFT2 => FCT2
Total Route step: 128
HA - edit route - 6sec
prtl3 - edit route - 2sec

Route name: FLOW#LFHNEE001144-01
Total Route step : 470 (it has sub-routes)
HA - edit route - 20sec
prtl3 - edit route - 3sec

Similarly Part X Route assignment for new part and route takes long time when compare to prtl3. 

Conclusion: If the number of route step increase then it takes long time in HA.
Could you please check if we can improve this.

column266:
10/Oct/17 9:35 PM;557058:b1a2c4a4-2e4d-47c5-a39a-ddb90b5e0886;This issue can summary as new added LDAP user will fail to login at first time in no CAS environment.

When userd added via user-maintenace, the user_ table will store a random password(placeholder as password field can not be empty), when login and authenticated LDAP server, Liferay will update password but in subsequent password retrieval, it still get previous password instead of updated password, cause Liferay local db authenticate failure.
column267:
13/Oct/17 3:24 AM;557058:b1a2c4a4-2e4d-47c5-a39a-ddb90b5e0886;To fix need to replace webapps/ROOT/WEB-INF/lib/portal-impl.jar with below two files:
com/liferay/portal/service/impl/[^UserLocalServiceImpl.class] 
com/liferay/portal/security/auth/[^LDAPAuth.class]

column1: Session Expired production.42-q
column37:
Session expires after 20min.

See the document [Session Expired production.42-q vs corpmesprtl3|https://docs.google.com/document/d/1lJ5UmjiAcBhBKl540Yni2rMtPhgmjmb-PEhrSK8Jl9k/edit?ts=59c13413] for more information.
column266:
06/Oct/17 5:42 PM;557058:93eaa1fe-a45e-4108-9ced-f012111a46fd;There are at least two ways to define the timeout. In our case, it being via <session-config> element in the /usr/local/liferay-portal/tomcat/webapps/ROOT/WEB-INF/web.xml. 
Please, change this setting to:
	<session-config>
		<session-timeout>60</session-timeout>
	</session-config>

Thanks, 
Welinton Coradini
Software Development Supervisor
US (CST), Mobile: +1 256 520-2704

column1: Production Scanning issues: "https" is not supported
column37:
from: Jimmie Jiang <jimmie.jiang@sanmina.com>
to:	"Keith Fuqua [42-Q]" <keith.fuqua@42-q.com>
cc:	"Gary.Li" <gary.li@sanmina.com>, Luke Henry <luke.henry@sanmina.com>, "Mike (Michael A.) Nashadka" <mike.nashadka@sanmina.com>, Fabio Pelissoni <fabio.pelissoni@sanmina.com>, Welinton Coradini <welinton.coradini@sanmina.com>, Eric Chong <eric.chong@sanmina.com>
date:	Mon, Aug 7, 2017 at 4:02 AM
subject:	Re: Production Scanning issues

There was a discussion between Gary and Luke. Luke granted the access for the palindrome registration and the command list could be able to display from the PS client now. As for another reported issue of the location/process field unable to load any values from the PS client through the given mes-api defined in the server info, it's confirmed as a code issue and require a new PS client package. Root cause was that the client doesn't support the 'https://' added in front of the mes-api host name in the server info, which caused a parser problem.

I was told that I am able to scan SN via the Device mode at this moment. I tried and it worked, except the attribute prompt being different with the attribute definition in mds. Jermy sent another email thread to Luke and Welinton and will discuss the issue there.

Jimmie Jiang
Sanmina Corporation
MES Business Systems Analyst
Skype: jimmie410

column1: Timeout in 42Q portal
column37:
from: Jasmine Zhu <jasmine.zhu@sanmina.com>
to: "Billy (Shiyuan) Huang" <billy.huang@sanmina.com>, Benny Deng <benny.deng@sanmina.com>, Eric Chong <eric.chong@sanmina.com>, Fabio Pelissoni <fabio.pelissoni@sanmina.com>, MES Support <mes.support@sanmina.com>
date:	Wed, Jul 26, 2017 at 9:06 PM
subject:	Timeout in 42Q portal

Hi Billy/Benny,

This is for the 42Q portal https://production.42-q.com.
E81 and E85 reported that the page timeout  frequently.
I tried myself, no matter I operate or not in the portal page, it will be timeout at about 20 minutes.

I checked the corpmesprtl3 page timeout setting, it sets as 60 minutes.
File: /usr/local/liferay-portal/tomcat/webapps/ROOT/WEB-INF/web.xml
        <session-config>
                <session-timeout>60</session-timeout>

File: /usr/local/liferay-portal/tomcat/webapps/cas/WEB-INF/spring-configuration/ticketExpirationPolicies.xml
     <!-- Expiration policies -->
        <bean id="serviceTicketExpirationPolicy" class="org.jasig.cas.ticket.support.MultiTimeUseOrTimeoutExpirationPolicy">
                <!-- This argument is the number of times that a ticket can be used before its considered expired. -->
                <constructor-arg
                        index="0"
                        value="1" />
                
                <!-- This argument is the time a ticket can exist before its considered expired.  -->
                <constructor-arg
                        index="1"
                        value="3600000" />
        </bean>
        
        <bean id="grantingTicketExpirationPolicy" class="org.jasig.cas.ticket.support.TimeoutExpirationPolicy">
                <!-- This argument is the time a ticket can exist before its considered expired.  -->
                <constructor-arg
                        index="0"
                        value="3600000" />
        </bean>


Could you help check why it is timeout in 20 minutes? And it seems operation in this portal does not help.

Thank you.

Regards,
Jasmine
column266:

Hi All,

We tried the 42Q portal link in chrome, it works , and we monitored for about 1 hour,it is not timeout.

Regards,

column1: Unit History of container serial
column37:
A container serial was displayed multiple times in Unit History report. 

 !image-2017-08-03-16-32-04-786.png|thumbnail!
column266:
03/Aug/17 5:39 PM;557058:c98ed516-b7be-460f-b3ae-d6d994e81951;The best way to get the container description should be from  from c_level.description, however this table is not replicated to mesr, so Unit History report was using mds_option table to get it.  The problem was that mds_option can have multiple entries for the same container types when report was expecting one per each. 
Per comment from MES dev and analysis the reference to mds_option table was removed from unit_history_complete functions and the fixed values used are now: 

 ('container_level',99,'LOT','LOT','LOT',1,'yes','')
,('container_level',100,'BOX','BOX','BOX',1,'yes','')
,('container_level',110,'SKID','SKID','SKID',1,'yes','')
,('container_level',120,'PALLET','PALLET','PALLET',1,'yes','')

We'll analyze the possibility of get the c_level table replicated.

column1: Print queue not configured properly in the production server
column37:
*Francisco's Comments: *
- The biggest issue is associated with travelers. Sometimes some print queues have some specific configuration and what I could see is that the plants are not performing label tests properly on UAT environment; few tests are done during UAT and most of the issues are addressed during go-live. It could be observed during E60 migration where we had to check how the print queues were configured on p3451ls1 and make the same configuration on Cirrus environment. Usually, MES Support does not check if print queue is properly configured before contacting Label team.
- I need to talk to Cesar about it... I will do that when I come back to Huntsville

Lake" <tom.lake@sanmina.com>, Juan Mejia <juan.mejia@sanmina.com>


Fabricio,

I need you work close to Hector to make sure we won't have have issues with any Label Engine travelers. As far as I remember, in the last migration tentative, the issues were tied to the print queues. I can remember that Tamas perfomed tests with some Label Engine travelers from his cube, but he did not realize production print queues had a different configuration from his print queue. Based on that, at that time, I asked Unix team to create new print queues with the proper configuration and the issue should gone.

Hector,

I know you will talk to Cesar, but better to consider additional tests to avoid issues. I do not know if the travelers from Label Engine were tested using the correct print queues. When we did some tests using our print queues worked properly, but we need to make sure the ones that will be used by production have the same configuration than Tamas' print queue. 

Questions, let me know.

Thanks,
Francisco

column1: Problems when creating or patching MESR DBs.
column37:
*Issue: *New functions and views are created or modified almost every day for reports, and updated in SVN  (trunk),  DBAs use a separated branch for patching and creating, but that is not updated very often, in some cases we've updated that branch directly to push fixes or new things to new DBs, which is I consider a bad practice and that has caused  problems.

*Proposed Resolution:*
From our side establish a process to regularly review it the with schema manager (creating a test DB). I already requested an update on that branch. Custom functions/ views will now manage in a custom schema.
column266:
03/Aug/17 5:56 PM;557058:c98ed516-b7be-460f-b3ae-d6d994e81951;The process to regularly review with schema manager (creating a test DB) before moving anything to the final branch is already in place. 
Plus, Custom functions/ views are being managed in a custom schema.

This task can be considered as complete.
